    "id": "scenario_nohup_background_jobs_133",
    "command": "nohup",
    "scenario": "Run long-running commands that continue after logout with nohup and background jobs.",
    "problem": "Need to start long tasks that survive SSH disconnection, run commands in background without terminal, manage job control, and prevent processes from being killed when terminal closes.",
    "solution": "Use nohup to ignore HUP signal, combine with & for background execution, redirect output appropriately, use disown for already-running jobs, and understand job control with jobs/fg/bg.",
    "steps": [
      "USER SAYS: 'I need to run a long script that takes hours, but I can\\'t keep my SSH session open. How do I make it survive disconnection?'",
      "AGENT: 'nohup is perfect for this! It makes processes immune to hangup signals.'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `nohup ./long-script.sh &`",
      "AGENT: '[1] 12345'",
      "AGENT: 'nohup: ignoring input and appending output to 'nohup.out\\''",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "AGENT: 'Process runs in background, survives logout!'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `jobs`",
      "AGENT: '[1]+  Running                 nohup ./long-script.sh &'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `nohup python3 train-model.py > training.log 2>&1 &`",
      "AGENT: 'Redirect both stdout and stderr to training.log'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `tail -f training.log`",
      "AGENT: 'Monitor progress in real-time'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `./script.sh &`",
      "AGENT: '[1] 12346'",
      "Run command: `disown`",
      "AGENT: 'Detach job from current shell (survives exit)'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `disown -h %1`",
      "AGENT: 'Keep job in jobs list but immune to HUP'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `jobs -l`",
      "AGENT: '[1]+ 12345 Running                 nohup ./long-script.sh &'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `fg %1`",
      "AGENT: 'Bring job to foreground'",
      "AGENT: 'Press Ctrl+Z to suspend'",
      "AGENT: '[1]+  Stopped                 ./script.sh'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `bg %1`",
      "AGENT: '[1]+ ./script.sh &'",
      "AGENT: 'Resume in background'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `nohup sh -c 'for i in {1..1000}; do echo $i; sleep 1; done' > count.log &`",
      "AGENT: 'Long-running loop'",
      "AGENT: ''",
      "Run command: `ps aux | grep nohup`",
